docs.abstract: The utility faces $30 billion in potential liability over deadly fires linked to its equipment. Critics say it is pressuring the state to shield it.
docs.snippet: The utility faces $30 billion in potential liability over deadly fires linked to its equipment. Critics say it is pressuring the state to shield it.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Pacific Gas and Electric said on Monday that it would seek bankruptcy protection as “the only viable option” as the giant California utility faces billions of dollars in liability claims from two years of deadly wildfires.

docs.abstract: The social network rolled out a redesign, in the most visible signal of how it is starting to emphasize private communications.
docs.snippet: The social network rolled out a redesign, in the most visible signal of how it is starting to emphasize private communications.
docs.lead_paragraph: MENLO PARK, Calif. — Mark Zuckerberg declared in March that he planned to shift Facebook away from being a public town square and to private communications. Now, the chief executive is rolling out the first in a series of changes to achieve that.

headline.main: Facebook Unveils Redesign as It Tries to Move Past Privacy Scandals

docs.abstract: North Dakota’s soybean crops are flourishing. But China has stopped buying.

docs.lead_paragraph: ARTHUR, N.D. — This is harvest season in the rich farmlands of the eastern Dakotas, the time of year Kevin Karel checks his computer first thing in the morning to see how many of his soybeans Chinese companies have purchased while he was sleeping.

headline.main: Their Soybeans Piling Up, Farmers Hope Trade War Ends Before Beans Rot
headline.print_headline: Tariffs Squeeze a Big Customer, But the Soybeans Keep Coming

docs.abstract: The social media company, which makes the Snapchat ephemeral messaging app, said on Tuesday that the flood of users who were leaving its platform had subsided.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Snap lost millions of users last year after an unpopular redesign of Snapchat, its ephemeral-messaging app. Now that exodus appears to be slowing.

docs.abstract: With its acquisition of two podcasting companies, the streaming service broadens its ambitions to include everything audio.
docs.snippet: With its acquisition of two podcasting companies, the streaming service broadens its ambitions to include everything audio.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Spotify began more than 10 years ago, it had a simple goal: to establish itself as a force in the music business by making millions of songs instantly available to listeners worldwide. But with its announcement on Wednesday that it had acquired two podcast companies, the streaming service sent a strong signal that it has broader ambitions.

headline.main: Spotify. It’s Not Just for Music Anymore.
headline.print_headline: With Deal for Podcaster,  Spotify Transcends Tunes
